apply spec-kit extension: to generate a file test-plan.md which includes unit tests and integration tests which later can be run in deployment pipeline in OpenShift
https://github.com/firstlast20200202/spec-kit/blob/main/extensions/EXTENSION-DEVELOPMENT-GUIDE.md
if commit in VScode UI takes forever, just open Terminal in it:
git add .
git commit -m "blabla"

extension structure
.specify/
└── extensions/
    └── my-ext/
        ├── manifest.yml           //important
        ├── my-ext-config.yml
        ├── templates/
        └── commands/
            └── testplan.md

Extension Configuration:
step 5:
$ cd <my-project>
$ specify extension add --dev ../spec-kit-practice/my-extension








